## Threat status and pressures

A total of 24 678 terrestrial taxa have been assessed in 2025 using the IUCN Red List of Threatened Species criteria. Of these, 14% of taxa are threatened, while in 2018, 13% of 22 667 assessed taxa were threatened. The overall increase in the proportion of species threatened is an indication of many vertebrates and plants becoming more threatened. The only new taxonomic group included are spiders (2 214 taxa) that have very low levels of threat at only 4%.

